Ha, welcome to the world of "phase 2".... soon every project will start as multi-phased...



I miss the good old days when I thought everything could be done in a one phase manner.... but after the paper plan hitting the skilled hands people's schedule best laid plans go out the window.


And on the taillights, find a quality local plastics shop, while not suitable for things that are easy to find, the price point for a set of lenses will probably be competitive given the exotic tax... a little fine detail cutting and bonding and you probably have enough in those broken ones to make a clean set.
